us.com/adsarchive/prints/trivial-pusiot-marilyn-manson-monroe-2522455/ Marilyn Manson-Monroe]{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> by Publicis Machine Johannesburg advertising agency (2015) \"Singer Marilyn Manson's head is attached to Marilyn Monroe's body\".\n* [[Unilever]]: Close-Up Toothpaste (2001) by [[J. Walter Thompson|JWT]]<ref>[https://archive.today/20130119145945/http://www.coloribus.com/adsarchive/tv-commercials/close-up-toothpaste-marilyn-monroe-19318/ \"Close-Up Toothpaste: Marilyn Monroe\" ''Coloribus''] February 23, 2010</ref>\n* [[Univision]]: \"Monroe It\" (2002) a blonde woman in a red dress gets it blown high<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lUgMrkQ_WsA Univision Girl \u2013 Monroe It \u2013 YouTube]</ref>\n* [[Visa Inc.|Visa]]: \"Signature Card\" (2004) by [[BBDO]]<ref>[http://www.marilynmonroe.com/business/ads/videoad1.html \"Campaigns\" ''MarilynMonroe.com''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100115015245/http://marilynmonroe.com/business/ads/videoad1.html |date=15 January 2010 }} February 24, 2010</ref>\n* [[Volkswagen]]: (2004)<ref>[http://www.marilynmonroe.com/about/viewheadline.php?id=533 \"Marilyn Monroe drives new television ad campaign for Volkswagen\" ''MarilynMonroe.com'']{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} February 19, 2010</ref>\n* [[Yuhan]]: Rapicold (2006) by [[WPP Group|Diamond Ogilvy]]<ref>[https://archive.today/20120720125340/http://www.advertolog.com/yuhan-corporation/print-outdoor/marilyn-monroe-256994/ \"Rapicol Cold Medicine: Marilyn Monroe\" ''Advertolog''] February 21, 2010</ref>\n\n==Architecture==\n* [[Absolute World]]: Building #4 and Building #5 are nicknamed \"Marilyn Monroe\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailycommercialnews.com/Home/News/2008/6/Absolute-Four-condominium-takes-shape-next-to-Marilyn-Monroe-towers-DCN028188W/|title=Absolute Four Condominium Takes Shape Next to 'Marilyn Monroe' Towers|publisher=[[Daily Commercial News]]|date=June 11, 2008|accessdate=August 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Art==\n* [[William Anastasi]]: ''Untitled'' (1995), and ''Untitled'' (1996)\n* Ashley Anderson: ''Shinobi Marilyn'' (2012)<ref>[http://www.gamescenes.org/2012/10/game-art-ashleys-andersons-shinobi-marilyn-2012.html Game Art: Ashley's Anderson's \"Shinobi Marilyn\" (2012)]</ref>\n* [[Clive Barker]]: ''MM'' (1999)\n* Cherie Bender: ''The Incandescents: Marilyn Monroe''<ref>[http://cheriebenderblog.blogspot.com/2009/11/incandescence-marilyn-monroe.html THE INCANDESCENTS: Marilyn Monroe; Nikola Telsa & Georgia O'keefe]</ref> (2009)\n* [[Peter Hill Beard]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1972)\n* [[Pierre Bellocq]]: ''Canvas of Stars'' [[mural]] for [[Gallagher's Steak House]] (2006)\n* [[Maurice Bennett]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (2011)<ref>[http://www.cnngo.com/shanghai/life/amazing-marilyn-monroe-toast-art-shanghai-525816 \"Amazing Marilyn Monroe Toast Art in Shanghai\" ''cnngo.com''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810163509/http://www.cnngo.com/shanghai/life/amazing-marilyn-monroe-toast-art-shanghai-525816 |date=10 August 2011 }} September 19, 2011</ref>\n* [[Pierre Bismuth]]:\n** ''Following the Right Hand of Marilyn Monroe in Some Like It Hot'' (2005)<ref>[http://www.artspace.com/pierre_bismuth/following_the_right_hand_of_marilyn \"Following the Right Hand of Marilyn Monroe\" ''artspace.com''] October 15, 2013</ref>\n** ''Following the Right Hand of Marilyn Monroe in The Misfits'' (2006)\n* [[Peter Blake (artist)|Peter Blake]]:\n** ''Marilyn Monroe Over a Painting No 1'' (1989\u20131990)\n** ''Marilyn Monroe Wall No 2'', \"MM Red Yellow\" (1990)\n** ''M for Marilyn Monroe''\n** ''H.O.M.A.G.E.'' (1991)\n* [[Pauline Boty]]: ''The Only Blonde in the World'' (1963) <ref name=\"google\">[https://books.google.com/books?id=EEgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA90&lpg=PA90&dq=Derek+Marlowe's+%22A+Slight+Misfit%22&source=bl&ots=fO8p0kdTLe&sig=SbzyVUQgBwnus68vfTIoHLST91U&hl=en&ei=VddSTr2BDsjjiAKh1a34DA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=