arilyn Monroe Nude'' (1990)\n** ''Marilyn'' (1991)\n** ''Poofie Print IV''<ref>[https://eolivia.com/scripts/prodList.asp?idCategory=48 \"Prints\" ''Olivia De Berardinis''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712004353/https://eolivia.com/scripts/prodList.asp?idCategory=48 |date=12 July 2015 }} July 9, 2015</ref>\n* [[Jerry De La Cruz]]: ''Monroe'' (2002)\n* [[Willem de Kooning]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1954)\n* [[Devon Dikeou]]: ''Marilyn Monroe Wanted to be Buried in Pucci'' installation (2008)<ref>[http://www.philau.edu/designcenter/exhibitions/maryline.html \"New York-Based Installation Artist Explores 1960s Fame, Fashion and Iconography\" ''TheDesign Center''] May 27, 2010</ref>\n* [[Dolk (artist)|Dolk]]: ''Pope Benedict XVI as Marilyn Monroe'' (2011)\n* [[Err\u00f3]]:\n** ''Daydream''\n** ''The Forgotten Future''\n** ''House of Gore''\n** ''Not Far Enough''\n** ''Your Love Don't Pay My Bills''\n** ''Sad Movies Make Me Cry'' (2001)\n* [[Jim Evans (artist)|Jim Evans]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1991)\n* [[Shepard Fairey]]: ''Marilyn Warhol'' (2000)<ref>[http://www.zarts.com/shepard-fairey/marilyn-warhol Shepard Fairey, ''Marilyn Warhol'' ''zarts.com''] August 22, 2011</ref>\n* [[Charles Fazzino]]:\n** ''Forever Marilyn'' (1998)\n** ''Love and Kisses, Marilyn'' (2008)\n* [[Audrey Flack]]: ''Marilyn: Golden Girl'' (1978)\n* [[Howard Finster]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1999)\n* [[James Gill (artist)|James Gill]]:\n** ''Marilyn Tryptych'' (1962) <ref name=\"google\" />\n** ''Pink Marilyn'' (2008)\n* [[Douglas Gordon]]: ''Self-Portrait as [[Kurt Cobain]] as [[Andy Warhol]] as [[Myra Hindley]] as Marilyn Monroe'' (1996)\n* [[Vladimir Gorsky]]: ''Marilyn Monroe''\n* [[Richard Hamilton (artist)|Richard Hamilton]]: ''My Marilyn'' (1966)\n* [[Keith Haring]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1981)<ref>[http://www.rfc.museum/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=189%3Akeith-haring&catid=264&Itemid=195 \"Keith Haring, Marilyn Monroe\" ''rfc.museum''] August 22, 2011</ref>\n* [[Margaret Harrison]]: ''Anonymous Was a Woman From [[Rosa Luxemburg]] to [[Janis Joplin]]'' (1977)\n* [[Gottfried Helnwein]]:\n** ''Boulevard of Broken Dreams'' (1984)\n** ''Marilyn'' (1992)\n* [[Al Hirschfeld]]: ''1954 Movies'' (1954)<ref>[http://www.alhirschfeldfoundation.org/search?keywords=MARILYN+MONROE \"Search Results: Marilyn Monroe\" ''alhirschfeldfoundation.org''] August 22, 2011</ref>\n* [[Jonathan Horowitz]]: ''Talking Without Thinking'' (2001)\n* [[Robert Indiana]]:\n** ''The Metamorphosis of Norma Jean'' (1998)\n** ''Marilyn, Marilyn'' (1999)\n** ''Sunburst Marilyn'' (2001)\n* [[John Seward Johnson II]]: ''[[Forever Marilyn]]'' (2011)<ref>[http://www.artmediaagency.com/en/23913/monumental-statue-of-marylin-monroe/ \"Monumental Statue of Marilyn Monroe\" ''Art Media Agency''] July 20, 2011</ref>\n* [[Ray Johnson]]: ''Dear Marilyn Monroe'' (1972)\n** ''Dear Marilyn Monroe/[[Chuck Close]]'' (1980)\n* [[Allen Jones (sculptor)|Allen Jones]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1960\u20131961)\n* [[Steve Kaufman]]:\n** ''Marilyn Monroe State'' (1995\u20131999)\n** ''Pop Marilyn''<ref>[http://www.stevekaufmanpopart.com/mm_state.html \"Marilyn Monroe\" ''stevekaufmanpopart.com''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111114175601/http://www.stevekaufmanpopart.com/mm_state.html |date=14 November 2011 }} August 3, 2011</ref>\n* [[Barbara Kruger]]: ''Not Stupid Enough'' (1997)\n* [[Sebastian Kr\u00fcger]]: ''Marilyn Monroe''\n* [[David LaChapelle]]: ''[[Amanda Lepore]] as Andy Warhol's Marilyn'' (2007)\n* [[Jean-Jacques Lebel]]: ''Taking a Real Good Peek at Marilyn's Amazing Offer'' (1961)\n* [[Zoe Leonard]]: ''Marilyn'' (1990\u20131995)\n* [[Richard Lindner (painter)|Richard Lindner]]: ''Marilyn Was Here'' (1970)\n* [[Gina Lollobrigida]]: ''My Friend, Marilyn Monroe'' (2003)\n* [[Bob Mackie]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1977)\n* [[Christopher Makos]]:\n** ''Andy Warhol Looks Like Marilyn Monroe'' (1982)\n** ''Andy Warhol 'I'm not Marilyn Monroe''' (1982)\n** ''Altered Images'' (19