ly, Starring MM and [[Brigitte Bardot|BB]]'' (1961)\n* [[Arnulf Rainer]]: ''Mythos Marilyn'' series (2002)\n* [[Mel Ramos]]: ''Peek-a-Boo'' series (2002)\n* [[Robert Rauschenberg]]: ''Test Stone #1'' (1967)\n* [[Tom Richmond (illustrator)|Tom Richmond]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1998)<ref>[http://www.tomrichmond.com/blog/tag/drawing-women/ Drawing Women ''tomrichmond.com''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100116083910/http://www.tomrichmond.com/blog/tag/drawing-women/ |date=16 January 2010 }} May 27, 2010</ref>\n* [[Faith Ringgold]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1997)\n* [[James Rosenquist]]: ''Marilyn Monroe I'' (1962) <ref name=\"google\" />\n* [[Mimmo Rotella]]:\n** ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1962)\n** ''Marilyn Decollage'' (1964)\n** ''I Vilti'' (1998)\n** ''Marilyn II'' (1979)\n** ''La Magnifica Preda'' (2004)\n* [[George Segal (artist)|George Segal]]: ''The Film Poster'' (1967)\n* [[Richard Serra]]: ''Marilyn Monroe-[[Greta Garbo]]'' (1981)\n* [[Cindy Sherman]]: ''Untitled'' (1986)\n* [[Roger Shimomura]]: ''Heroine, Hammer, Hibachi\" (1987)\n* [[Hajime Sorayama]]: ''Sexy Robot in Yellow'' (album cover of [[Aerosmith]]'s ''Just Push Play'')\n* [[Daniel Spoerri]]:\n** ''The Spirit of Marilyn Captured by Merlin'' (2003)\n** ''Merlin Meets Marilyn'' (2003)\n** ''Der Teddybar von MM'' (2003)\n* [[John Stango]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (2010)\n* [[Brett-Livingstone Strong]]: ''Tribute to Marilyn Monroe'' (1989)\n* [[Harold Town]]: ''Superstar'' (1970)\n* [[Jacques Villegl\u00e9]]: ''Marilyn'' (1982)\n* [[Wolf Vostell]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' (1962)<ref>[http://collections.walkerart.org/item/object/7098 \"Marilyn Monroe Wolf Vostell\" Walker Art Center] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930134825/http://collections.walkerart.org/item/object/7098 |date=30 September 2011 }} August 5, 2011</ref>\n* [[Erik Wahl]]: ''Untitled'' (2012) (bought by [[Pink (singer)|Pink]])\n* [[Kerry Waghorn]]: ''Marilyn Monroe''<ref>[http://www.kerrywaghorn.com/caricatures_actors.htm \"Actors Caricatures\" ''kerrywaghorn.com''] May 27, 2010</ref>\n* [[Petrus Wandrey]]: ''Memento-Marilyn-Monroe'' (2003)\n* [[Andy Warhol]]:\n** ''[[Marilyn Diptych]]''\n** ''Twenty-five Colored Marilyns'' (1962)\n** ''[[Shot Marilyns]]''\n** ''[[Untitled from Marilyn Monroe]]''\n* [[Tom Wesselmann]]: ''Marilyn in Bed'' (1984)<ref>[http://www.phillipsdepury.com/auctions/lot-detail/TOM-WESSELMANN/UK010407/315/10/1/12/detail.aspx \"Tom Wesselmann\" ''phillipsdepury.com''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004064901/http://www.phillipsdepury.com/auctions/lot-detail/TOM-WESSELMANN/UK010407/315/10/1/12/detail.aspx |date=4 October 2011 }} August 22, 2011</ref>\n* [[Stephen B. Whatley]]: ''40th Anniversary Tribute'' (2002)<ref>[http://www.stephenbwhatley.com/pic59.htm ''Stephen B. Whatley''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016043936/http://www.stephenbwhatley.com/pic59.htm |date=16 October 2013 }}</ref>\n* [[Jon Whitcomb]]:\n** ''Untitled'' (1958) (owned by [[Joe DiMaggio]])<ref>[http://www.huntauctions.com/online/view_lots_items_list_closed.cfm?auction=27&start_number=801&last_number=900 \"Items For The Auction of May 19th & 20th, 2006\" HuntAuctions.com] February 25, 2010</ref>\n** Cover and illustrations for the March 1959 ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]''\n* [[Susan Dorothea White]]: ''The Crowning with Sexism'' (1994)\n* [[Willard Wigan]]: ''Marilyn Monroe on a Diamond'' (2007\u20132008)<ref>[http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/os-ripleys-collection-of-william-wegan-miniatu-018,0,3698857.photo \"The Wee Works of Willard Wigan\" ''The Orlando Sentinel''] October 15, 2013</ref>\n* [[Erwin Wurm]]: ''Thinking About Marilyn'' (2003)\n* [[Jean-Pierre Yvaral]]: ''Marilyn Monroe'' series (1990\u20131994)<ref>[http://www.robertsandelson.com/artists/Yvaral/work1.htm \"Yvaral\" ''Robert Sandelson Gallery''] January 3, 2014</ref>\n* [[Zevs (artist)|Zevs]]: ''Visual Violation \u2013 Marilyn Monroe'' (2011)<ref>[http://www.artspace.com/zevs/visual_violation_marilyn_monroe \"Visual Violation \u2013 Marilyn Monroe, 2011, by Zevs\" ''artspace.com''] October 15, 2013</ref>\n\nSee also: ''Marilyn in Art'' Roger Taylor (Ed.), Chaucer Press (2006), {{ISBN|1-904957-02-1|978-1-904957-02-7}}\n\nSee also: ''Elvis + Marilyn: 2x Immortal'' Geri DePaoli (Ed.), [[RCS MediaGroup|Rizzoli]] (1994), {{ISBN|0-8478-1840-3}}\n\n==Celebrities as Monroe==\n* [[Amy Lee]]: dressed as Monroe (according to her she's called \"Scarilyn Monroe\") from ''The Seven Year Itch''<ref>[http://starslikemarilyn.blogspot.com/2009/11/amy-lee.html The Stars like Marilyn Monroe Amy Lee]</ref> for the Halloween Party in 2007\n* [[Anna Nicole Smith]]: aspired to be her favorite blonde Marilyn Monroe<ref>[http://krhughestlburns.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/annanicolesmith-050693-jpg_215850.jpg Anna Nicole Smith]</ref>\n* [[Christina Aguilera]]: for the June 2006 ''[[GQ]]''\n* [[Courtney Stodden]]: dressed as Monroe from ''The Seven Year Itch'' wearing clear platform heels<ref>[https://www.stereogum.com/1757698/courtney-stodden-dressed-as-marilyn-monroe-for-some-reason/vg-loc/videogum/ Courtney Stodden Dressed As Marilyn Monroe For Some Reason]</ref> in 2012.\n* [[Drew Barrymore]]: for the September 1996 ''[[George (magazine)|George]]''\n* [[Barbara Walters]]: as Monroe from ''Gentlemen Prefer Blondes''<ref>[https://starslikemarilyn.blogspot.com/2009/05/barbara-walters.html Stars like Marilyn Monroe Barbara Walters]</ref> from a Halloween episode of ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]'' in 2003.\n* [[Beyonc\u00e9]]: for the May 2014 ''[[Out (magazine)|Out]]''\n* [[Lara Bingle]]: for the August 2008 ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Australian Cosmopolitan]]''\n* [[Hillary Clinton]]: retouched photo aping the \"subway grate\" pose from ''The Seven Year Itch'' on the October 1995 ''[[Spy (magazine)|Spy]]''\n* [[Hugh Hefner]]: wants to be buried next to Monroe's<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/hugh-hefner-buried-marilyn-monroe-article-1.3526691|title=Hugh Hefner planned to be buried next to this iconic sex symbol|first=Jessica|last=Chia|date=28 September 2017|publisher=|via=Daily News}}</ref> gravestone when he dies. Hefner passed away in 2017.\n* [[Mariah Carey]]: paid homage to Marylin's 1953 visit to U.S. troops in Korea in her \"[[I Still Believe (Brenda K. Starr song)#Mariah Carey version|I Still Believe]]\" music video.\n* [[Cindy Crawford]], [[Daryl Hannah]], [[Ashley Judd]], and [[Heather Locklear]]: for the May/June 1997 ''American Photo''\n* [[Miley Cyrus]]: for the March 2014 ''[[Vogue (magazine)|German Vogue]]''\n* [[James Franco]]: at the [[83rd Academy Awards]]<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5BkQ6ltiClI \"Oscars 2011 / Anne Hathaway and James Franco Host\" ''www.youtube.com''] November 1, 2010</ref>\n* [[French and Saunders|Dawn French and Jennifer Saunders]]: aped \"Two Little Girls from Little Rock\" from ''Gentlemen Prefer Blondes''<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HK1NN8Msfeo \"French & Saunders: Marilyn Monroe & Jane Russell\" ''youtube.com''] May 26, 2010</ref>\n* [[Jade Goody]]: as ''[[Marilyn Diptych]]'' for ''[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|The Daily Star]]''\n* [[Rachel Hunter]]: dressed as Monroe in an episode of the British reality competition series [[Stars in Their Eyes|Celebrity Stars in Their Eyes]] in 2000.\n* [[Rudolph Giuliani]]: for the 1997 New York Inner Circle press dinner<ref>[http://www.nbcnews.com/id/18108978 \"Rudy Giuliani in a Dress: Will Voters Care?\" ''nbcnews.com'']  February 20, 2010</ref>\n* [[Sharon Osbourne]]: dressed as Monroe as she is lip synching to ''Diamonds Are a Girl's Best Friend'' during their 2nd Annual Rocktober Lip Sync War on an episode of ''[[The Talk (talk show)|The Talk]]''<ref>[http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/halloween-2016-celebrities-show-off-costumes/2/ Halloween 2016: Celebrities show off costumes]</ref> in 2016.\n* [[Paris Hilton]]: for the August 2010 launch of her [[perfume]], Tease<ref>[https://archive.today/20120913091323/http://www.showbizspy.com/article/209882/paris-hilton-pretends-to-be-marilyn-monroe-at-fragrance-launch-pics.html \"Paris Hilton Pretends To Be Marilyn Monroe at Fragrance Launch\" ''showbizspy.com''] August 11, 2010</ref>\n* [[Nicole Kidman]]: for the March 2008 ''[[Harper's Bazaar|Harper's Bazaar Australia]]''\n* [[Lindsay Lohan]]: recreated [[The Last Sitting]] with photographer [[Bert Stern]] for the February 25, 2008 ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]''\n** for the July 2009 ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue Espa\u00f1a]]''\n** for the January/February 2012 ''[[Playboy (magazine)|Playboy]]''\n* [[Jennifer Lopez]]: paid homage to \"Happy Birthday, Mr. President\" on the April 22, 2010 ''[[George Lopez|Lopez Tonight]]''<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FdnN7Ub8Mcs \"Jennifer Lopez Surprises George Lopez\" ''youtube.com''] April 28, 2010</ref>\n* [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]: for the April 1991 ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' shot by [[Steven Meisel]]\n* [[Katie Couric]]: Dressed as Monroe from ''Gentlemen Prefer Blondes'' for ''The Today Show'' Halloween episode in 2005.<ref>[http://www.eonline.com/photos/3002/celebs-channel-marilyn-monroe/113995 Celebs Channel Marilyn Monroe Katie Couric]</ref>\n* [[Kylie Minogue]]: regularly performs as Monroe<ref>[https://archive.today/20120717204214/http://sydney.citysearch.com.au/music/1137592126005/Kylie:+Top+10+Live+Performances \"Kylie: Top 10 Live Performances\" ''sydney.citysearch.com''] March 19, 2010</ref>\n* [[Andreja Peji\u0107]]: \"Marilyn Off Duty\" shoot for the October 2011 ''Lovecat Magazine''\n* [[Lisa Marie Presley]]: for [[Herb Ritts]] and made-up by [[Kevyn Aucoin]]<ref>[http://www.ifge.org/books/making_faces.htm \"Making Faces by Kevyn Aucoin\" ''ifge.org''] March 25, 2010</ref>\n* [[Britney Spears]]: performed \"[[If U Seek Amy]]\" as Monroe on her [[Femme Fatale Tour]]\n* ''The Seven Year Itch'' \"subway grate\" pose has been aped by numerous celebrities, including [[